ities. Upon completion of the course, you will be awarded a <a href="https://cpduk.co.uk/providers/the-mandatory-training-group" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">CPD-UK accredited</span></i></a> certificate earning you 15 CPD hours, demonstrating your commitment to professional development and adherence to the highest standards of learning. To earn your certificate, you must complete an online assessment and achieve a minimum score of 80%. This ensures that you have absorbed the course material and are ready to put your knowledge into practice.<br><br>In order to gain full training qualifications, we recommend completing an Award in Education (AET) after completing your train-the-trainer accreditation.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-74_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-76_">The added value of a system </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_added_value_of_a_system_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691758443" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_added_value_of_a_system_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691758443 1536w" width="2098" height="1293" alt="The added value of a system - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The added value of a system - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-77_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-78_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Using the train-the-trainer approach, organisations or individuals can assemble a <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/education-and-training/how-the-train-the-trainer-model-develops-a-pool-of-internal-trainers" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">pool of trainers</span></i></a> efficiently, resulting in faster training. With qualified instructors, you can train more people faster and at a lower cost. All of our courses are delivered on our easy-to-use  